<br>
1. If you have a scanner place them out in paint or paintshop pro and make boxes around the characters and delete anything you dont want with an ease square mager.<br>
<br>
2. Same thing on paper but this would mean to sktech lightly.. -.-...im not to found of going back over in ink ACK! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=neosolaris>Neo Solaris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/17/03 4:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2520.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Manga comic drawing</span><hr size=1> Hmmm so what size would you reccomend the boxes be... in CM? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=alucard1515>alucard1515</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator <img src=http://contest.polykarbon.com/badge1.gif></span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/17/03 6:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2520.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.undeadart.com/forum/alucard.gif width=100 height=94></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Manga comic drawing</span><hr size=1> There isn't a set size, and if there was, it'd be the most boring looking comic ever. Make them bigger or smaller as necessary. Vary the shape and proportions. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kjirra>kjirra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/18/03 8:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2520.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Manga comic drawing</span><hr size=1> when you have a pic that's rather important you should make those bigger and when they aren't so important they can be small. Sounds logic <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=higakun>higakun</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://komplx.com/higan/Page_2/IMAG000.JPG" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/18/03 8:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2520.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://images.warcry.com/image.php?id=4964 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Manga comic drawing</span><hr size=1> look at the masters. thats the best advise. otomo. clamp. ect.... and like the first rely said, customize and mimic. do whats best for the scene, if its intense make the whole page a box. if you are telling a range of actions and want to get your point across right away, then you may have up to 10 boxes in no real style. or a quick action consisting of about three to five blocks. and its just me, but i personally like to add som boxes with no frame. the picture continues on and you can see some of it in between the other boxes. clamp's CLOVER is a good example of unique boxes. but find a manga that is simialr to your style and see what is generally used and making sure not to rip off the original. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lostnchii>LostNChii</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fresh Meat</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/22/03 1:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2520.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   I'm working on my first ever manga comic</span><hr size=1> After a period of flatlining, a crazy idea spun into my little teeny brain :P  to do a manga.  I came up with everything I needed for the comic, and I have finally finished the rough ^.^<br>
Any of you more experianced people have advice for a beginning manga artist? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mrcynic1776>mrcynic1776</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/26/03 5:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2520.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I'm working on my first ever manga comic</span><hr size=1> Learn storytelling and pacing from the Masters.  Otomo Katsuhiro, Clamp, Will Eisner.<br>
<br>
Don't mock someone else art.  Get your style down.<br>
<br>
Don't just draw big eye.  Manga is speedlines, aspect to aspect panel transitions, tones, and iconic charcterization.<br>
<br>
Good Luck <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showPrevMessage?topicID=2520.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showNextMessage?topicID=2520.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2520.topic&index=9><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.emailToFriend?topicID=2520.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.threadControl?topicID=2520.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2520.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2520.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub25.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="polykarbonbbsfrm18">PK